    "description": "<p>Usercentrics is a market leader in the area of enterprise consent management platforms (CMP) and empowers companies to obtain, manage and document the consent of their users across platforms. Usercentrics’ solution is easy-to-implement, fully customizable and legally compliant.</p>\n<p>We’re looking for an energetic and creative Team Lead Software Engineer (m/f/d) to join our team located in the centre of Munich! Revolutionising an entire industry is exciting, but not easy. That’s why we need you! Become a part of our international team and let our enthusiasm infect you as we build the leading consent software!</p>\n<p>#Your Responsibilities</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Leading a team that consists of supportive and passionate software engineers (local and remote)</li>\n<li>Orchestrating the design, development and delivery of our data service products.</li>\n<li>Collaborating with PM/Product Owner and other developers, guide through to planning and grooming sessions and drive team’s discussions on system architecture and component design</li>\n<li>Support and guide the team to ensure all committed stories for the sprint are completed per the sprint goal</li>\n<li>Reviewing other team members’ code and providing corrections and feedback in a professional, skill-building way</li>\n<li>Driving innovation and continuous improvement by empowering and enabling your team.</li>\n<li>Taking over the responsibility for performance management and career development of your team.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>#You Have</p>\n<ul>\n<li>5+ years of experience writing and deploying high-quality production code combined with object-oriented software design abilities.</li>\n<li>2+ years of experience in technical leadership and people management of at least 3-5 team members</li>\n<li>In-depth knowledge of React or Angular ( Typescript, Node.js is nice to have )</li>\n<li>Agile development experience and focus on UI</li>\n<li>Have a product-oriented mindset: you like offering technical solutions to business problems.</li>\n<li>Type S(tartup) personality: smart, ethical, friendly, hard-working and proactive.</li>\n<li>Hands on experience with GraphQL and/or MongoDB is a plus.</li>\n<li>Experience with GCP or another cloud provider (AWS, Azure, …) is a plus.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>#Your Perks</p>\n<ul>\n<li>A fantastic team, flat hierarchies &amp; lots of freedom to be creative</li>\n<li>Flexible working hours incl. the option for home office</li>\n<li>Great events with a fun and enthusiastic team and trainers, massages, meditation</li>\n<li>Subsidised gym memberships and a weekly lunch by our personal happiness manager</li>\n<li>Central in one of Munich's top locations incl. a great office</li>\n</ul>\n",
