    "title": "[CDI] Full Stack Developer",
    "description": "<p><strong>[CDI] Full Stack Developer</strong></p>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://api.video/\">api.video</a> connects people through their cameras. Join us to build the first worldwide video backbone!</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>We are an <strong>API-first platform to manage online video</strong> and our goal is to become a new standard, such as Stripe for the payments, Twilio for text and VOIP or Sendgrid for email.</li>\n<li>We are building our own <strong>EDGE infrastructure</strong> to provide unprecedented performances on the market.</li>\n<li>We have raised a <a href=\"https://techcrunch.com/2020/06/24/api-video/\"><strong>$5.5M Seed Round</strong></a> in June 2020 from Blossom Capital, Kima Ventures and some <a href=\"https://www.crunchbase.com/funding_round/api-video-angel--81c5d31d\"><strong>incredible Angels</strong></a>.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>By joining us, you will work in an international environment, addressing challenges that will impact millions of people.</strong></p>\n<p>You will join the Growth team composed of the Product Designer, the Growth Manager, 2 Developer Evangelists and the Marketing Manager.\nYou will be the very first Developer Full Stack, so you will manage all the process and documentation.</p>\n<p><strong>Your missions</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>You lead the new back office development.</li>\n<li>You develop, maintain and modify dedicated tools and landing pages to help our developer community.</li>\n<li>You maintain and improve the api.video website.</li>\n<li>You proceed to tests to ensure compliance for all developments and you produce a detailed documentation.</li>\n<li>You create excellent interactions from designs, writing reusable content modules and maintainability of the code.</li>\n<li>You create usable, responsive and interactive interfaces across multiple devices.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Your profile</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>+4 years of experience as a Full Stack Developer.</li>\n<li>Deep knowledge in Javascript/Typescript, CSS3, Sass/SCSS, HTML5 and NodeJS ecosystem.</li>\n<li>Knowledge of basic SEO principles.</li>\n<li>Experience in PHP development and SQL.</li>\n<li>Excellent knowledge of browser troubleshooting and debugging practices and techniques.</li>\n<li>Knowledge in API integration is a plus.</li>\n<li>Knowledge of DatoCMS (optional).</li>\n<li>English proficiency.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Package</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Competitive pay and equity.</li>\n<li>Annual Bonus.</li>\n<li>Covered medical, dental, and vision benefits.</li>\n<li>Company Provided Equipment.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>The position is based in Bordeaux, France.</p>\n<p><strong>Are you up for the challenge?</strong>\nApply now via the <a href=\"https://ltpx.nl/DD4ACw6\"><strong>application form</strong></a>.</p>\n<p>api.video is an equal opportunity employer. All applicants will be considered for employment without attention to race, color, religion, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, national origin, veteran, or disability status.</p>\n<p><em>Agency calls are not appreciated.</em></p>\n",
